  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n## 2026-04-29 17:04 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 2] The probation-band rescue is real, but it still weakens the cleaner >=50 book\n\n**Task:** Re-test whether the weak `45-49.9` PM smart-entry band can be selectively rescued with price/persistence filters, and check that against the smaller live-tagged V5a sample before touching production logic.\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive (`pm-bot`, `hl-bot`).\n- In the full `03h-shadow-sim-results.csv` sample, the raw probation band is still weak at **98 trades / 60.2% WR** versus **294 trades / 86.4% WR** for `abs_bias >= 50`.\n- The best rescue pocket I found was **`0.495 <= yes_price < 0.525` plus persistence `3-16`**, which lifts the probation band itself to **40 trades / 72.5% WR**.\n- But the important test failed: adding that rescued subset back into the stronger `>=50` book drops the combined cohort to **334 trades / 84.7% WR**. The tighter `0.50-0.52` version still falls to **85.0% WR**. So the rescue helps the weak bucket in isolation, but still dilutes the better book.\n- A recent 14-day recheck says the same thing: rescued probation trades get to **70.6% WR**, but `>=50` alone is still materially cleaner at **83.7% WR**, and the merged set slips to **81.8% WR**.\n- I sanity-checked the smaller live-tagged V5a sample in `confidence_outcomes.jsonl` so I would not overfit the 03 UTC shadow regime into current live hours. That sample is too thin to override the shadow result: only **4 current-hour (`11/12/20`) probation trades** exist, even though they happened to go **3/4**.\n- I wrote the full artifact to `/home/ubuntu/clawd/research/p2-smart-entry-analysis-2026-04-29.md`.\n\n**My thinking:** There is a genuine mid-strength pocket inside `45-49.9`, but it is not elite enough to earn promotion. If the rescue subset still drags down the better `>=50` cohort, then we are just adding complexity to justify weaker trades. The tiny current-hour live sample also means I should not pretend we have production-grade evidence either way yet.\n\n**Decision:** Do **not** add a special rescue rule for `45-49.9`, and do **not** make a production threshold edit from this heartbeat alone. Keep the band on probation in research, and keep looking for improvements in spacing/regime controls rather than trying to save borderline bias prints.\n\n**Next:** On the next P3 heartbeat, switch to strategy work per rotation. When P2 comes back around, join the V5a-tagged live outcomes to `v5b_tag` and cooldown state to test whether spacing/regime gating is the real source of improvement instead of the bias floor itself.\n\n\n## 2026-04-29 05:03 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 1] BTC lost clean bearish whale consensus, but ETH / SOL / HYPE stayed decisively short\n\n**Task:** Run a fresh Pillar 1 copy-intel pass, quantify the current HL leaderboard by notional instead of just headcount, and decide whether the new PM mixed bullish print is strong enough to challenge the whale book.\n**Findi",
